#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:2
msgid "How to get help"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:4
msgid ""
"If you need assistance with one of your contributions, there are a few "
"places you can go for help."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:7
msgid "How to find maintainers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:9
msgid ""
"For better efficiency and a higher chance of success, you should try "
"contacting individuals or groups with more specific knowledge first:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:11
msgid ""
"If your contribution is for a package in Nixpkgs, look for its maintainers "
"in the [`maintainers`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#var-meta-"
"maintainers) attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:14
msgid "Check if any teams are responsible for the relevant subsystem:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:15
msgid "On the [NixOS website](https://nixos.org/community/#governance-teams)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:16
msgid ""
"In the [list of Nixpkgs maintainer teams](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/"
"blob/master/maintainers/team-list.nix)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:17
msgid ""
"In the `CODEOWNERS` files for [Nixpkgs](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/"
"blob/master/ci/OWNERS) or [Nix](https://github.com/NixOS/nix/blob/master/."
"github/CODEOWNERS)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:19
msgid ""
"Check the output of [`git blame`](https://git-scm.com/docs/git-blame) or "
"[`git log`](https://www.git-scm.com/docs/git-log) for the files you need "
"help with. Take note of the email addresses of people who committed relevant "
"code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:22
msgid "Which communication channels to use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:24
msgid ""
"Once you've found the people you're looking for, you can contact them on one "
"of the [community communication platforms](https://nixos.org/community):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:26
msgid "[GitHub](https://github.com/nixos)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:28
msgid ""
"All the source code is maintained on GitHub. This is the right place to "
"discuss implementation details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:31
msgid ""
"In issue comments or pull request descriptions, [mention the GitHub username]"
"(https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/writing-on-github/getting-started-"
"with-writing-and-formatting-on-github/basic-writing-and-formatting-"
"syntax#mentioning-people-and-teams) found in the [`maintainers-list.nix` "
"file](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/maintainers/maintainer-"
"list.nix)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:33
msgid "[Discourse](https://discourse.nixos.org)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:35
msgid ""
"Discourse is used for announcements, coordination, and open-ended questions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:37
msgid ""
"Try the GitHub username found in the [`maintainers-list.nix` file]"
"[maintainers-list] to mention or directly contact a specific user. Note that "
"some people use a different username on Discourse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:40
msgid "[Matrix]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:42
msgid "Matrix is used for short-lived, timely exchanges, and direct messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:44
msgid ""
"To contact a maintainer, use their Matrix handle found in the [`maintainers-"
"list.nix` file][maintainers-list]. If no Matrix handle is present for a "
"specific maintainer, try searching for their GitHub username, as most people "
"tend to use the same one across channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:47
msgid "Maintainer teams sometimes have their own public Matrix room."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:49
msgid "Email"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:51
msgid "Use email addresses found with `git log`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:53
msgid "Meetings and events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:55
msgid ""
"Check the [official NixOS Calendar](https://calendar.google.com/calendar/u/0/"
"embed?src=b9o52fobqjak8oq8lfkhg3t0qg@group.calendar.google.com) and the "
"[Discourse community calendar](https://discourse.nixos.org/t/community-"
"calendar/18589) for real-time or in-person events. Some community teams hold "
"regular meetings and publish their meeting notes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:58
msgid "Other venues"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:60
msgid ""
"If you haven't found any specific users or groups that could help you with "
"your contribution, you can resort to asking the community at large, using "
"one of the following official communication channels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:62
msgid "A room related to your question in the [NixOS Matrix space][matrix]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:63
msgid ""
"The [*Help* category](https://discourse.nixos.org/c/learn/9) on Discourse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/how-to-get-help.md:64
msgid ""
"The general [`#nix`](https://matrix.to/#/#nix:nixos.org) room on Matrix."
msgstr ""
